# RNA-seq Analysis Pipeline (Bash-Orchestrated HPC Version)

## Project Objective
The goal of this pipeline is to provide a **reproducible, scalable, and modular workflow for RNA-seq analysis** in a High-Performance Computing (HPC) environment. It automates:

- Quality control of sequencing reads  
- Adapter trimming  
- Alignment to reference genomes  
- BAM post-processing (sorting, indexing)  
- Gene quantification (count matrices)  
- Differential expression analysis  
- Visualization and reporting  

The pipeline ensures that large transcriptomic datasets are processed efficiently, reproducibly, and in a format suitable for collaborative research and downstream publication.

## Stakeholders
- **Computational Biologists / Bioinformaticians:** Develop and run RNA-seq analysis.  
- **Lab Scientists / Wet-Lab Teams:** Provide sequencing datasets and interpret results.  
- **Data Scientists / Statisticians:** Perform downstream statistical analysis and visualization.  
- **Project Managers / Collaborators:** Monitor pipeline progress and results for decision-making.  
- **IT / HPC Administrators:** Maintain HPC infrastructure, user access, and scheduling efficiency.  

## Pipeline Overview & Flow
This **Bash-orchestrated pipeline** is modular, HPC-ready, and reproducible. Each step is isolated in Conda environments, wrapped as HPC jobs, and orchestrated via a master runner script.

```text
FASTQ (raw reads)
      |
      v
[Quality Control] --> FastQC
      |
      v
[Adapter Trimming] --> Trimmomatic / Cutadapt
      |
      v
[Alignment] --> HISAT2
      |            \
      v             --> BAM (SAMtools)
[Post-processing] --> Sort & Index BAM
      |
      v
[Feature Counting] --> featureCounts (Count matrix)
      |
      v
[Differential Expression] --> DESeq2 (R)
      |
      v
[Visualization & Reporting] --> Heatmaps, Venn diagrams, Volcano plots
rna_seq_pipeline/
├── README.md
├── environment/          # Conda YAML files / Dockerfile
├── scripts/
│   ├── bash/             # HPC wrapper scripts
│   ├── r/                # Statistical analysis scripts (DESeq2)
│   └── python/           # QC / preprocessing scripts
├── data/                 # Raw / small test datasets
├── results/              # Output BAMs, count matrices, figures
├── docs/                 # Metadata, pipeline decisions, reports
├── config/               # Sample info, reference paths, cluster config
├── workflow/             # Optional workflow files
├── logs/                 # HPC job logs
└── run_pipeline.sh       # Main orchestrator script
